# shadcn/ui Conventions

Shared UI primitives live in `apps/web/src/shared/ui/` and follow the shadcn/ui pattern: Radix primitives + `class-variance-authority` (cva) for variants + `cn()` (clsx + tailwind-merge) for class composition.

## File Layout

```text
apps/web/src/shared/ui/
  button.tsx
  dialog.tsx
  input.tsx
  ...
src/shared/lib/cn.ts   # the cn helper
```

- One primitive per file. Filename `kebab-case`, exported component `PascalCase`.
- Feature code (in `src/features/*`) MUST import from `src/shared/ui` before building local variants.

## `cn` Helper

```ts
// src/shared/lib/cn.ts
import { clsx, type ClassValue } from "clsx";
import { twMerge } from "tailwind-merge";

export function cn(...inputs: ClassValue[]) {
  return twMerge(clsx(inputs));
}
```

## Component Pattern (cva + Radix Slot)

```tsx
import * as React from "react";
import { Slot } from "@radix-ui/react-slot";
import { cva, type VariantProps } from "class-variance-authority";
import { cn } from "@/shared/lib/cn";

const buttonVariants = cva(
  "inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-md text-sm font-medium transition-colors disabled:opacity-50",
  {
    variants: {
      variant: {
        default: "bg-brand-gold text-white hover:bg-brand-gold/90",
        ghost: "hover:bg-brand-gold/10",
      },
      size: { sm: "h-8 px-3", md: "h-10 px-4", lg: "h-12 px-6" },
    },
    defaultVariants: { variant: "default", size: "md" },
  },
);

type ButtonProps = React.ComponentProps<"button"> &
  VariantProps<typeof buttonVariants> & { asChild?: boolean };

export function Button({ className, variant, size, asChild, ref, ...props }: ButtonProps) {
  const Comp = asChild ? Slot : "button";
  return <Comp ref={ref} className={cn(buttonVariants({ variant, size }), className)} {...props} />;
}
```

## Rules

- Use Radix primitives (already installed: `@radix-ui/react-*`) for accessibility-critical components: Dialog, DropdownMenu, Tooltip, Tabs, etc.
- Use `asChild` + `Slot` so consumers can pass `<Link>` or other components without nested DOM.
- Use React 19's ref-as-prop (no `forwardRef`).
- Export the `cva` variants object alongside the component when consumers may need to reuse classes (e.g. `buttonVariants`).
- Keep variant tokens in sync with `@theme` tokens — do not hardcode colors that exist as Tailwind tokens.
- Do NOT install raw shadcn components blindly. Strip example comments, align color tokens with our `@theme`, and remove unused variants.
